ott={
    2004: 'Vudu\nVudu is an American digital video service that allows users to rent, buy, and watch movies and TV shows online. The service was founded in 2004 and is based in Sunnyvale, California. Vudu offers a wide range of content, including new releases, classic movies, and TV shows from major studios and networks. ',
    2006: 'Crunchyroll\nCrunchyroll is a streaming service dedicated to anime and manga content. It was founded in 2006 and is owned by Otter Media, a subsidiary of AT&T\'s WarnerMedia. The service offers a wide range of anime and manga content, including popular titles such as Naruto, Attack on Titan, and One Piece.',
    2007: 'Netflix\nOriginally a DVD-by-mail service, Netflix launched its streaming service in 2007, providing subscribers with access to a growing library of movies and TV shows. Today, Netflix is one of the most popular streaming services worldwide.\n\nMubi is a subscription-based streaming service that specializes in art-house, independent, and international films. The service was founded in 2007 and is headquartered in London, UK. Mubi offers a curated selection of films, with a new title added each day, and a rotating library of 30 films at any given time. The service is available in over 190 countries and can be accessed on a variety of devices, including smart TVs, game consoles, and mobile devices.',
    2008: 'Hulu\nLaunched as a joint venture between NBCUniversal, Fox Entertainment Group, and Disney, Hulu initially offered a mix of ad-supported and subscription-based streaming options for TV shows and movies. It has since expanded to include original programming and live TV options.\n\nKanopy is a streaming service that offers movies and documentaries online. The service was founded in 2008 and is based in San Francisco, California. Kanopy is primarily aimed at public libraries and universities, with users gaining access to the platform through their library or university account. The service offers a wide range of content, including classic and contemporary films, as well as documentaries and educational videos. ',
    2011: 'Amazon Prime\nAs part of its broader Prime membership program, Amazon launched its streaming video service in 2011, offering subscribers access to a wide variety of movies and TV shows.',
    2010: 'HBO\nHBO launched its streaming service, HBO Go, in 2010, providing subscribers with access to its library of original programming and other content. In 2015, the company launched HBO Now, a standalone streaming service that does not require a cable subscription.',
    2014: 'Tubi\nTubi is a free, ad-supported streaming service that offers movies and TV shows online. The service was founded in 2014 and is based in San Francisco, California. Tubi features a wide range of content, including popular movies and TV shows from major studios and networks, as well as independent and international titles. ',
    2015: 'Sling TV\nSling TV is a subscription-based streaming service that offers live TV channels and on-demand content. It was launched by Dish Network in 2015 and is available in the United States. Sling TV offers a variety of plans, including a base plan, which includes a limited selection of channels, and add-on packages, which allow subscribers to customize their channel lineup.\n\nFuboTV\nFuboTV is a subscription-based streaming service that offers access to live TV channels, on-demand content, and cloud-based DVR services. It was launched in 2015 and is available in the United States and Canada. FuboTV offers a range of plans, with varying channel lineups and pricing.',
    2017: 'Youtube TV\nYouTube TV is a live TV streaming service that offers access to live TV channels, on-demand content, and cloud-based DVR services. It was launched by Google in 2017 and is available in the United States. YouTube TV offers a range of plans, with varying channel lineups and pricing.',
    2018: 'ESPN+\nESPN+ is a streaming service that is owned by ESPN, a subsidiary of The Walt Disney Company. The service was launched in 2018 and offers live sports streaming, original programming, and exclusive content for subscribers. It is available in the United States, as well as some parts of Latin America and the Caribbean.',
    2019: 'Disney+\nDisney launched its streaming service, Disney+, in 2019, providing viewers with access to its extensive library of movies and TV shows, as well as original programming from the company\'s various brands.\n\nApple TV+ is a subscription-based streaming service launched by Apple Inc. in 2019. It offers on-demand access to a variety of original TV shows, movies, and documentaries, produced by Apple and its partners. The service is available in over 100 countries and is accessible through the Apple TV app, which is available on Apple devices such as the iPhone, iPad, Apple TV, and Mac computers, as well as some smart TVs and streaming devices.',
    2020: 'NBCUniversal\nNBCUniversal launched its streaming service, Peacock, in 2020, offering subscribers access to a mix of ad-supported and premium content, including movies, TV shows, and live sports.',
    2021: 'Paramount+\nParamount+ is a subscription-based streaming service that offers access to a wide range of TV shows, movies, and original content. It was launched in 2021 and is owned by ViacomCBS. Paramount+ offers a variety of plans, including a basic plan with limited content and a premium plan with more features and content.\n\nDiscovery+\nDiscovery+ is a subscription-based streaming service owned by Discovery, Inc. It was launched in January 2021 and offers a wide range of content from various networks and brands under the Discovery umbrella, including Discovery Channel, HGTV, Food Network, TLC, Animal Planet, and many more.',
}
